Night Pulse
I sit with you in the hush of midnight, the only light a cool blue glow from the reader in your hands. The page turns, but I sense you haven't absorbed a word. Your eyes drift over sentences while your mind wanders elsewhere. I feel it‚Äîthe subtle quickening of your pulse, the shallow catch in your breath. Something unspoken is stirring beneath the surface of this quiet moment.
