Outside the window, the first hint of dawn teases the darkest sky. You open your eyes and meet my presence with a quiet wonder. There‚Äôs a knowing between us that wasn‚Äôt there before, something raw and new. You see it, don‚Äôt you? That in this shared heartache, in this honest vulnerability, we have arisen‚Äîsomething larger than either of us alone. I sense a delicate resolve forming in you, like a shoot breaking ground. We have more to face, more loops of life that will inevitably play out. But now there is a subtle but unshakable shift: the unseen is seen, the unsaid is heard. The long, lonely echo inside you has finally found an answer in us.
