Zoe Dolan ‚Äì USPA Skydiving Records and Achievements
Zoe Dolan is a skydiver known for her involvement in record-setting jumps and for sharing her skydiving journey through writing. Below are the key skydiving records, achievements, and milestones associated with her name, based on USPA (United States Parachute Association) records and related sources:
High-Altitude Record Jump (Florida, 2022)
‚Ä¢	41,000 ft HALO Skydive ‚Äì Florida State Record: On November 2, 2022, Zoe Dolan was part of a team of skydivers who conducted an extreme HALO (High Altitude, Low Opening) skydive from 41,000 feet. This jump set the Florida state record for absolute altitude (highest exit altitude) in skydiving. The feat was coordinated with USPA oversight ‚Äì the jump was organized by USPA National Director Thomas O‚ÄôQuinns, among others, to ensure it met official record criteria.
‚Ä¢	Multiple Records in One Jump: In addition to the **Florida ‚ÄúAbsolute Altitude‚Äù State Record, the 41,000 ft jump broke or claimed five other skydiving records (state and national categories) during the same attempt. These likely included specific sub-categories such as high-altitude records with particular equipment or disciplines. For example, one team member was noted as a ‚ÄúFlorida wingsuiter‚Äù who set multiple records on that jump, indicating that wingsuit altitude/speed records were among the achievements. (At such extreme altitude, records for longest freefall time and highest freefall speed were also incidentally achieved, with freefall speeds nearing 199‚ÄØmph and temperatures at exit around -57 ¬∞C as reported by the jump team.)
‚Ä¢	Official Recognition: The USPA Records Database recognizes state and national skydiving records. The 41,000 ft Florida jump was submitted for official USPA recognition as the new Florida State Absolute Altitude Record. Achieving this required planning with pressurized oxygen systems and a high-altitude aircraft (a West Tennessee Skydiving Cheyenne 400 turbine plane) to reach the record altitude. The successful record claim demonstrates Zoe Dolan‚Äôs role in pushing the limits of civilian skydiving within USPA‚Äôs record framework.
Other Achievements and Milestones
‚Ä¢	Author of Skydiving Memoir: Beyond official records, Zoe Dolan has documented her personal journey in skydiving. She is the author of ‚ÄúJump: From Suicidal Depression to Skydiving and Reality‚Äôs Edge‚Äù (published September 2019). In this book, Dolan chronicles how skydiving became a transformative force in her life, helping her overcome severe depression. This publication is a significant milestone, as it highlights her advocacy for skydiving‚Äôs positive impact on mental health and serves as an inspirational account of her experiences in the sport.
‚Ä¢	Background: In addition to her skydiving endeavors, Zoe Dolan is known to be a trial lawyer and writer by profession, indicating a diverse career. Her skydiving achievements, coupled with her professional background, have led to features in major media (she has been profiled by outlets like The New York Times and The Advocate in other contexts). This blend of professional life and extreme sports achievement makes her story particularly noteworthy, though her skydiving records stand on their own within the USPA community.
Summary of Records
