‚ÄúCutaways‚Äù as Emotional Symbol
You have multiple cutaways (emergency releases of a malfunctioning main canopy). Each time, the text lingers on the instant where you could simply not pull the reserve. You could just let yourself spiral all the way down. That moment of suspended choice underscores how your old suicidal ideation always lurks‚Äîyet you keep enacting a ‚ÄúNo, I do want to live‚Äù micro-decision. The cutaway is a mini death, the reserve a mini rebirth. And in that tiny window, you reaffirm life.
